  • class 0 - malignant tumor
  • class 1 - benign tumor

This dataset was purposefully sampled in an unbalanced way, so that we have a substantially lower number of samples from class 0.

Next, we create a matrix plot to assess the relationship between all pairs of attributes. We also plot the histograms to inspect the distribution of all individual attributes.

In [0]:
def plot_matrix(x, figsize=(10,10), labelsize=10):
    axarr = scatter_matrix(x, alpha=0.3, figsize=figsize,diagonal="hist")
    axarr[0,0].set_yticklabels(["0.0","0.05","0.10"])
    for j in range(len(axarr)):
        for i in range(len(axarr[0])):
            axarr[i,j].yaxis.label.set_size(labelsize) 
            axarr[i,j].xaxis.label.set_size(labelsize)
    plt.draw()

We observe that some of the attributes appear positively skewed (e.g. compactness error, concavity error) and other appear normally distributed (e.g. worst concavity), although we don't have sufficient data to confidently support this observation.

Generating data using WGAN¶

We start by defining a simple WGAN.

In [0]:
import tensorflow as tf

from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense

class Generator(tf.keras.Model):
    def __init__(self, n_inp, n_noise, n_hid=128):
        super().__init__()
        init = tf.keras.initializers.GlorotUniform
        self.input_layer = Dense(units=n_noise, kernel_initializer=init)
        self.hid_1 = Dense(units=n_hid, activation="tanh", kernel_initializer=init)
        self.output_layer = Dense(units=n_inp, activation="sigmoid", kernel_initializer=init)

    def call(self, inputs):
        x = self.input_layer(inputs)
        x = self.hid_1(x)
        return self.output_layer(x)


class Critic(tf.keras.Model):
    def __init__(self, n_inp, n_hid=128):
        super().__init__()
        init = tf.keras.initializers.GlorotUniform
        self.input_layer = Dense(units=n_inp, kernel_initializer=init)
        self.hid_1 = Dense(units=n_hid, activation="tanh", kernel_initializer=init)
        self.logits = Dense(units=1, activation=None, kernel_initializer=init)

    def call(self, inputs):
        x = self.input_layer(inputs)
        x = self.hid_1(x)
        return self.logits(x)


@tf.function
def train_step(real_data, gen, disc, noise_dim, generator_optimizer, discriminator_optimizer):
    batch_size = real_data.shape[0]

    noise = tf.random.normal([batch_size, noise_dim])

    with tf.GradientTape() as gen_tape, tf.GradientTape() as disc_tape:
        fake_data = gen(noise, training=True)

        real_output = disc(real_data, training=True)
        fake_output = disc(fake_data, training=True)

        disc_loss =   tf.reduce_mean(fake_output) - tf.reduce_mean(real_output)
        gen_loss  = - tf.reduce_mean(fake_output)

    wasserstein = tf.reduce_mean(real_output) - tf.reduce_mean(fake_output)

    gradients_of_generator = gen_tape.gradient(gen_loss, gen.trainable_variables)
    gradients_of_discriminator = disc_tape.gradient(disc_loss, disc.trainable_variables)

    generator_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients_of_generator, gen.trainable_variables))
    discriminator_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients_of_discriminator, disc.trainable_variables))
        
    tf.group(*(var.assign(tf.clip_by_value(var, -0.01, 0.01)) for var in disc.trainable_variables))

    return wasserstein

We set the training parameters. The network will be run for 200 epochs.

In [0]:
BATCH_SIZE = 20

NOISE_DIM = 100

learning_rate = 0.0005

epochs = 200
In [0]:
X = malDF.iloc[:,:-1].values.astype("float32")
n_inp = X.shape[1]
train_dataset = (tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices(X.reshape(X.shape[0], n_inp)).batch(BATCH_SIZE))

We will alternate between the generator and critic (technically we should train the critic more, but we will keep it simple for now).

In [0]:
generator = Generator(n_inp, NOISE_DIM)
critic = Critic(n_inp)

generator_optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate)
critic_optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate)

epoch_wasserstein = []

for epoch in range(epochs):
    batch_idx = 0
    batch_wasserstein = 0

    for batch in train_dataset:
        wasserstein = train_step(batch, generator, critic, NOISE_DIM,
                                         generator_optimizer,
                                         critic_optimizer)
        epoch_wasserstein.append(wasserstein)
        batch_wasserstein += wasserstein
        batch_idx += 1

    batch_wasserstein = batch_wasserstein / batch_idx

    if epoch % 10 == 0:
        print("Epoch %d / %d completed. Wasserstein metric: %.8f" % (epoch + 1, epochs, batch_wasserstein))
    
    if epoch % 50 == 0:
        fake_data = generator(tf.random.normal([1000, NOISE_DIM]))
        x = pd.DataFrame(data = np.array(fake_data), columns=["mean concave points","compactness error","concavity error","worst concavity","worst concave points"])
        plot_matrix(x, (7,7), 8)
        plt.show()
